name: Outrageous Acts of Science
overview: Scientists and amateurs conduct experiments and post their exploits online. Each episode counts down 20 popular Internet videos and explains the science behind them.

episodes.name: Hackaverse
episodes.overview: Inflatable snowmobile; trolley rocket; bedbug tattoos; car driven by an Ipod.

episodes.name: Heroes and Hoaxers
episodes.overview: Featuring musical fruit and a shark balancer.

episodes.name: Greatest Hits II
episodes.overview: Scientists select the best clips from season 2.

episodes.name: Fact or Fake
episodes.overview: The Web's most unbelievable videos! Can our team of experts spot the fakes? Features underwater BASE jumping and the world's most amazing pool trick shot.

episodes.name: License to Thrill
episodes.overview: A man pops wheelies with a car; a man is taped to a ceiling; BASE jumpers go to extremes.

episodes.name: Kings of Creation
episodes.overview: A car that jumps rope; a Japanese robot that never loses "Rock Paper Scissors"; a one-wheeled motorbike; rocket boots.

episodes.name: Born to Be Wild
episodes.overview: A woman who lived through an avalanche; a man who can hold his breath for over 22 minutes; a daredevil who walks between two hot air balloons thousands of feet in the air.

episodes.name: Cowboys of Chaos
episodes.overview: A homemade cannon; exploded homes; and magnets that can crush a hand.

episodes.name: Epic Fails
episodes.overview: A surfing mishap; the world's toughest tongue-twister; and a man's fear of lobsters.

episodes.name: Urban Legends
episodes.overview: A dangerous electric bike; a human-powered submarine; and a life-sized Lego car.

episodes.name: Fact or Fiction
episodes.overview: Are these incredible web clips fakes or not? Our team of scientists spots the hoaxes. Featuring skiing in Hawaii, a wingsuit pilot towed by a car, a close encounter with a great white shark, vertical driving, and the most amazing handgun trick shot ever.

episodes.name: Speed Freaks
episodes.overview: We're going faster, further, and weirder than ever before! Featuring a man who drives his car 1,000 feet over water, a shrimp with the fastest punch in the animal kingdom, bionic boots, and a car that jumps over a plane.

episodes.name: Home Hacks
episodes.overview: The best backyard geniuses online! Featuring motorcycle chariot racing in Florida, a man who gives his friends a lift with his homemade Iron Man-style exoskeleton, a plane that flies without wings, and a 9-foot-high robotic insect.

episodes.name: Like a Boss
episodes.overview: Find out how to do it like a boss. Features a record-breaking butt skipper, a woman restraining four motorcycles, and the fastest downhill bike ride ever. These guys reveal the very best of human ingenuity and perseverance by doing it like a boss.

episodes.name: Is this for Real?
episodes.overview: We separate science fact from science fiction. From a woman who walks on water and a man that pumps up inner tubes with his ears, our experts ask "are they for real?," and expose the internet's best tricksters.

episodes.name: Man vs. Nature
episodes.overview: A glass-breaking gorilla and a speed-racing sea lion face off against a snowman in the desert and an underwater wheelchair.

episodes.name: Epic Skills
episodes.overview: We countdown the clips that show off the Internet legends with the most epic skills on the planet: the world's most incredible skin, the world's first tattooing toes, and a speed flier that lands inside a moving cable car.

episodes.name: Homemade Hotshots
episodes.overview: A countdown the most amazing and dangerous home experiments; mixing electricity with swimming pools; racing supercharged golf carts on the dragway; setting off homemade gunpowder.

episodes.name: Wild Rides
episodes.overview: Snowboarding in the clouds; quad bike riding with a koala; looping a car in a sphere.

episodes.name: Killer Builds
episodes.overview: A countdown of the best builds on the web; a seafaring supercar; bees that can 3D print, jet powered wings that can make a man fly.

episodes.name: Facepalm
episodes.overview: A close call with a humpback whale; a plane with circular wings; painful ant bites; and a glow stick explosion.

episodes.name: Shock & Awesome
episodes.overview: Included: a communicating crow; super speedy tractor; silly putty axe; monster crane lift; and surfing motorcycle.

episodes.name: Food Fight
episodes.overview: The science behind Internet food videos.

episodes.name: More Than Meets the Eye
episodes.overview: The craziest optical illusions and visual tricks on the Internet are counted down.

episodes.name: Not Safe for Work
episodes.overview: We’re counting down the most amazing – and dangerous – workplace clips. From office pranks, and lifesaving drones to construction site skills. This is as far from your typical 9 to 5 as it’s possible to get! These guys are working it!

episodes.name: Wild Things
episodes.overview: A quest to find crazy critters and weird natural events; kangaroos in a bag, swimming under ice and a subterranean hot air ballooning world record.

episodes.name: Beast Mode
episodes.overview: Putting the human body to the test; skill, strength and intelligence; tongue twisting tricks to human flight.

episodes.name: Punked?
episodes.overview: A countdown of Internet clips; revolutionary reversing; fish out of water; a bizarre six-pack; experts separate fact from fiction.

episodes.name: Nailed It
episodes.overview: The Internet's biggest stunts and builds; featuring skiing acrobatics, memory skills and a kite surf stunt.

episodes.name: Garage Genuis
episodes.overview: Searching the world's garages, backyards and basements to find home inventors; items include a super strong model truck, a carnival ride and a backyard apocalypse bunker.

episodes.name: Man vs. Animal
episodes.overview: A countdown of the wildest animal videos on the Internet.

episodes.name: Don't Tell Mom
episodes.overview: On this very special Mother's Day edition of Outrageous Acts of Science, we count down stunts you'd never want your mom to see.

episodes.name: Game Changers
episodes.overview: Prepare to follow in the wake of the some of the internet’s most ingenious trend setters. We’ve got never-before-done barrel rolls, dizzying experiments in space, and a bungee jump like no other. We're going to the cutting edge -- and beyond.

episodes.name: Neighborhood Watch
episodes.overview: We celebrate the scientific world in our own backyards with some of the wildest homemade Internet videos. Meet the suburban scientists who bathe in Silly Putty and the daredevils who build flying bikes, and find out the truth behind backyard UFOs.

episodes.name: Beta Testers
episodes.overview: Beta Testers: Problem-solve with some of the best inventors on the web. We watch as these ambitious creators test a kit to fend off sharks, skydive without parachutes, and build DIY scuba gear.

episodes.name: Fearless or Foolish
episodes.overview: We’re turning the spotlight on both fearless and foolish internet legends. We’ll see heart stopping trick shots, extreme mountain unicyclers, and a relaxing hot bath of chilli sauce. These epic skills and fails prove science is one tough Task Master.

episodes.name: Amped Up
episodes.overview: We’re showcasing the most inventive people on the web. People who’ve taken a simple idea and turned it up to 11! We’ll learn how to get a tattoo from a machine, build an engine from paper, and ride on a giant homemade swing.

episodes.name: Truth or Troll
episodes.overview: Can a saw made of paper cut wood? Can you take a selfie with a tornado? Do giant gators roam Florida's golf courses? Our experts are on a mission to find the truth and expose the web's greatest trolls.

episodes.name: Natural Selection
episodes.overview: We’re on an internet expedition in search of Mother Nature’s biggest OMG moments. We’ve got cuddly bears, criminal ferrets and an entire island made from trash. We’re on the quest for the weirdest, wildest and wackiest nature lovers on the internet.

episodes.name: Epic Elements
episodes.overview: Spotlighting pioneers who have wrestled with the forces of the universe and faced the elements in order to capture something extraordinary.

episodes.name: Moguls of Mayhem
episodes.overview: A countdown of clips celebrating the fearless innovators who have a genius for anarchy and destruction. From real-life hungry hippos to a firearm symphony shootout, these kings of carnage will showcase science in its most explosive form.

episodes.name: Pure Power
episodes.overview: Plug in and witness these mighty individuals as they harness the speed, strength, and skills required to blow the lid off the internet. We'll see outrageous bungee jumps and powerful drones that can fly and swim.

episodes.name: Bucket List
episodes.overview: We're creating the ultimate bucket list. We'll learn how to cook bread with a volcano, build underwater hotel rooms, and go eyeball-to-eyeball with Great Whites.

episodes.name: Mind Benders
episodes.overview: We're about to blow minds with some of the most mind-bending clips on the web. Our experts taste-test a 100-year-old cracker, witness a real-life transformer car, and listen to guitars played underwater.

episodes.name: Life Hackers
episodes.overview: We're turning the spotlight on backyard inventors that are creating the ultimate life hacks. We'll see these geniuses turn a bike into a car, soda into a fire extinguisher, and a jet ski into a Jetovator.

episodes.name: Tons of Anarchy
episodes.overview: All things carnage; the world's biggest firework; a watermelon-destroying vacuum cannon; a giant fire tornado; anarchy and chaos.

episodes.name: Bragging Rights
episodes.overview: Counting down highly skilled show-offs; people who claim their epic skills give them serious bragging rights; tandem unicycles; high altitude dinner parties; archery with a twist.

episodes.name: Body Rockers
episodes.overview: Counting down just how far the limits of the human body can be pushed; experts test homemade gas masks and create music from blood; the most extreme body experiments on the web.

episodes.name: Masters of Disasters
episodes.overview: A countdown of the most dangerous clips on the web; fearless people who have mastered disaster by turning it into a scientific endeavor; explosive artwork, underwater sword swallowing and a jumbo jet pulled by just one man.

episodes.name: Supernatural
episodes.overview: Mother Nature's most amazing moments are featured. Included: a man eaten alive by leaches; a rainbow at night; and a man who pulls a car with his eye sockets.

episodes.name: Quantum Leaps
episodes.overview: A look at quantum leaps.

episodes.name: Make It Real
episodes.overview: The spotlight is focused on inventors changing the world one creation at a time. The expert builders behind flying motorcycles, giant fighting mega robots and rock climbing cars all feature.

episodes.name: Unusual Suspects
episodes.overview: Following strange clips lurking in the shadows. Also: the crazy science behind snoring hummingbirds; bands performing underwater; and alligators frozen alive in ice.
